  "text": "The current studies have potential therapeutic implications. Although currently available TZDs are effective insulin sensitizers, they are also associated with side effects including weight gain, increased adiposity, and edema. It would therefore be desirable to develop selective PPARγ modulators that retain antidiabetic and antiatherogenic activities but do not have undesirable side effects. In this regard, it has recently been demonstrated that a selective PPARγ modulator that is relatively ineffective in promoting transcriptional activation is fully active as an inducer of PPARγ-mediated repression of inflammatory response genes by promoting ligand-dependent sumoylation of PPARγ [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] , suggesting the possibility of new avenues for development of safer, more effective drugs.",
